    "spell_type": "spell",
    "subtype": "spell",
    "targets": "one creature or object",
    "text": "You unleash a sickly gray beam of toxic spores at your target. Make a spell attack against the target. If you hit a non-magical object that\u2019s made of organic material (such as a tree, wooden house, or massive skull), it melts away into a foul-smelling sludge. A single casting can destroy no more than a 10-foot cube of matter.   \n  \nIf you hit a creature, it takes 6d12 poison damage and 6d12 spirit damage with a basic Fortitude save. If you critically hit, the target gets a result one degree of success worse than the outcome of its Fortitude save.",
